## Layout

```
{{workspace_path}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                       # this file
├── .claude/
│   ├── skills/  agents/  docs/     # deployed by /setup-workspace
│   ├── memory/                     # workspace MEMORY/lessons
│   ├── settings.json
│   └── projects-index.json         # project registry
├── workstreams/                    # open-item ledgers per workstream (gitignored)
├── sessions/active/                # advisory markers (gitignored)
├── collected/                      # skill data (gitignored)
├── artifacts/                      # skill / workstream outputs (gitignored)
├── contributions/                  # staged contributions (gitignored)
├── me/                             # identity, brag log, growth, team
├── source/                         # boilerplate source repos
└── projects/                       # registered projects (gitignored)
```

### Artifacts naming

Any output produced by a skill or session — feedback files, generated documents, collected data, derived artefacts — lands under an `artifacts/` directory, never co-located with `workstreams/` or `sessions/`. Artefacts mirror their scope, exactly like workstreams, sessions, and memory: workspace-scoped artefacts at the workspace root, project-scoped artefacts under the project.

| Output type | Path pattern |
|-------------|--------------|
| Skill output, workspace scope | `artifacts/<skill-slug>/<filename>` (e.g., `artifacts/one-on-one-prep/2026-05-11-jane.md`) |
| Skill output, project scope | `projects/<project-slug>/artifacts/<skill-slug>/<filename>` |
| Workstream artefact, workspace scope | `artifacts/<workstream-slug>/<filename>` |
| Workstream artefact, project scope | `projects/<project-slug>/artifacts/<workstream-slug>/<filename>` |

Separation of concerns: `workstreams/` files are open-item ledgers that `/bye` writes into; mixing observational output pollutes that lifecycle. Resolve scope from the session marker, never from cwd.

